So we must split paths at the `if` and at exception points. However, per instructions, we analyze *all execution paths in the function*. Since Java exception paths are implicit and not syntactically linear, standard static resource leak analysis (e.g., as in FindBugs/SpotBugs) treats the `try` block as having:
